@startuml 16-process-introspection
title JOTP: Process Introspection (ProcSys Pattern)
skinparam backgroundColor #f0f0f0
skinparam sequence {
    BoxBackgroundColor LightBlue
    LifeLineBorderColor DimGray
    LifeLineBackgroundColor White
}

participant Operator as "Operations\nTeam"
participant ProcSys as "ProcSys\n(introspection)"
participant "Proc<S,M>\n(running)"
participant "Supervisor\n(monitoring)"

autonumber

note over Operator, "Proc<S,M>\n(running)"
  ProcSys enables live runtime introspection
  WITHOUT stopping or restarting the process
  (Unlike debugging which typically stops execution)
end note

Operator ->> ProcSys: getState(procRef)
activate ProcSys

ProcSys ->> "Proc<S,M>": inspect()
activate "Proc<S,M>"

note right of "Proc<S,M>"
  Capture current state
  without blocking
  message loop
end note

"Proc<S,M>" ->> ProcSys: return S (state object)
deactivate "Proc<S,M>"

ProcSys ->> Operator: State { value: 42, mode: ACTIVE }
deactivate ProcSys

note right of Operator
  Can examine state
  in production
  without downtime
end note

---

Operator ->> ProcSys: suspend(procRef)
activate ProcSys

ProcSys ->> "Proc<S,M>": pauseMailboxLoop()
activate "Proc<S,M>"

note right of "Proc<S,M>"
  Pause message handling
  but keep process alive
  (messages queue up)
end note

"Proc<S,M>" ->> ProcSys: suspended
deactivate "Proc<S,M>"

ProcSys ->> Operator: ok
deactivate ProcSys

note right of Operator
  Process suspended
  Messages accumulate
  in mailbox
end note

---

Operator ->> ProcSys: statistics(procRef)
activate ProcSys

ProcSys ->> "Proc<S,M>": captureStats()
activate "Proc<S,M>"

note right of "Proc<S,M>"
  Collect metrics:
  - message queue depth
  - uptime
  - memory usage
  - message count
end note

"Proc<S,M>" ->> ProcSys: Stats { queueDepth: 5, uptime: 3600s }
deactivate "Proc<S,M>"

ProcSys ->> Operator: Statistics object
deactivate ProcSys

note right of Operator
  Use stats for alerting:
  - queue building up?
  - process leaking memory?
  - message throughput OK?
end note

---

Operator ->> ProcSys: resume(procRef)
activate ProcSys

ProcSys ->> "Proc<S,M>": resumeMailboxLoop()
activate "Proc<S,M>"

note right of "Proc<S,M>"
  Resume message handling
  Process accumulated
  messages in order
end note

"Proc<S,M>" ->> ProcSys: resumed
deactivate "Proc<S,M>"

ProcSys ->> Operator: ok
deactivate ProcSys

note right of Operator
  Process back to normal
  Message ordering
  preserved (FIFO)
end note

---

note over Operator, "Supervisor\n(monitoring)"
  INTEGRATION: Supervisor uses ProcSys
  to diagnose why children are failing
  before deciding restart strategy
end note

"Supervisor\n(monitoring)" ->> ProcSys: getState(failedChild)
"Supervisor\n(monitoring)" ->> ProcSys: statistics(failedChild)

note right of "Supervisor\n(monitoring)"
  Decision logic:
  - if queue depth = max?
    → child is bottleneck, restart
  - if uptime < 1s?
    → rapid failures, delay restart
  - if error count high?
    → strategy-dependent recovery
end note

@enduml
